(77, NULL, NULL, 'Peter W.', 'peterwalwal@hotmail.com', 1399154400, 'We only had one night inbasel as we traveled back to Munich, but we had a great experience. Location was great, easy walk to town, clean comfortable rooms.', 'Hotels', 39, '10', '10', '10', '9', '10', 9.8, 'Yes'),
(78, NULL, NULL, 'Nadia', 'nadianadoro@yahpp.com', 1399154400, 'Breakfast value was superior with a beautiful selection of buffet items. Hotel staff was extremely accommodating with the exception of Housekeeping. While the room was cleaned daily to my satisfaction for the most part, linens were not changed despite our request, extra bottles of conditioner were removed from my room (despite my previous request specifically', 'Hotels', 39, '4', '4', '6', '6', '9', 5.8, 'Yes'),
(79, NULL, NULL, 'Tariq Malik', 'takaa@gmail.com', 1399154400, 'I stay here for 3 nights in Feb2014, the hotel location is ideal - close to the financial DIST and shopping street Orchid, close by to two MRT stations Basha and Dhobighat. Rooms and service is excellent , at the moment construction of MRT is taking to the adjacent land , which may noisy during the day , during the night sleep no trouble at all.', 'Hotels', 40, '3', '9', '8', '3', '1', 4.8, 'Yes'),
(80, NULL, NULL, 'Zea', 'zee2@gmail.com', 1399154400, 'We had a wonderful stay and would definitely go back. The hotel food is disappointing but there are lots of places to dine within walking distance. The staff are friendly and professional. Loved the comfy bed and pillows.', 'Hotels', 40, '4', '3', '3', '2', '8', 4, 'No'),
(81, NULL, NULL, 'ambahall', 'ambhook@gmail.com', 1399154400, 'My clients Professor and Mrs Ell stayed one night at this hotel. Professor Ell lodged his visa debit card for security. A visa debit card is - or should be - internationally recognised. Certainly he could use his card for shop purchases in Singapore without a problem - there was more than sufficient money in his account. However, the Rendezvous could', 'Hotels', 40, '2', '2', '9', '10', '9', 6.4, 'Yes'),
(82, NULL, NULL, 'Beano', 'beanpa@yahoo.com', 1399154400, 'This was my 2nd stay at Rendezvous. Obviouslyl I like it or I wouldn''t go back. BUT, the price is a big reason why I choose this place. There are much nicer, more modern hotels in Singapore, but this hotel is convenient to MRT and Bugis, has comfy, well-appointed rooms and very good service. The gym is the worst feature - the renovation obviously did', 'Hotels', 40, '3', '8', '6', '7', '6', 6, 'Yes'),
(83, NULL, NULL, 'S N Saggar', 'myohdleo@hotmail.com', 1399154400, 'We had room facing garden & swimming pool. Requested non smoking Twin beds. Vey comfortable. No traffic noise in spite of main road location. Ideal for visit Little India & China Town. Taxi ride to China Town from hotel cost £5 only but little India within walking distance. Under ground MRT station less than 5 minutes walk from the hotel.', 'Hotels', 40, '10', '10', '10', '10', '10', 10, 'No'),
(87, NULL, NULL, 'azxcd', 'johnaz@gmail.com', 1427206714, 'gewg', 'Hotels', 35, '1', '4', '3', '4', '5', 5.6, 'Yes'),
(89, NULL, NULL, 'Mohie65', 'Mohie65@gmail.com', 1439816280, 'We visited with friends for five nights towards the end of April, the cottage is new, large and very well appointed it carries all the creature comforts for an enjoyable vacation. The location just off the highway in Bandrol is superb, a stones throw away from Naggar and Kullu with stunning views of the surrounding mountains. \nLoved the stone exterior and all wood flooring in the cottage. Also an ideal getaway as you are not in the hustle and bustle of the two major towns of Kullu and Manali but both are very accessible for food and recreation.', 'Tours', 36, '1', '1', '1', '1', '1', 6, 'Yes'),
(90, NULL, NULL, 'Heather C', 'Heathe@email.com', 1439816499, 'Our first family (children aged 5,8,11) trip to India surpassed our expectations! This cottage was to European standards but was next to a local residence so you feel you have a genuine experience. From the cottage we had great trips to the Buddhist monastery, \r\nThe Owners orchard in the Hills, shopping for scarves in Kullu and the Hindu temple and hustle and bustle in Manali were all highlights but the great cultural experience and spectacular views are the real secret!\r\n\r\nI''d highly recommend this cottage - don''t forget some warm clothes as well as your summer ones!', 'Tours', 36, '', '', '', '', '', 8, 'Yes'),
(91, NULL, NULL, 'SahilAdlakha', 'SahilAdlakha@gmail.com', 1439816696, 'One of the cosiest places I have stayed in.Perfect for an artist or a writer. Actually the best place to sit and read all day.If you sleep with the curtains open in the small room its actually like sleeping under the stars.Small is beautiful ! Perfect fireplace, interiors and great terrace. Am coming back shortly', 'Tours', 36, '', '', '', '', '', 8, 'Yes'),
(92, NULL, NULL, 'jamshaid', 'jamshaid@hotmail.com', 1439817108, 'Surender was a genuinely wonderful host, he made himself available at 5am in the morning when I arrived and then fixed me a delicious omelette as I was hungry from the trip. During my stay there, he was readily helping with my various questions and requests for assistance. The room and the bathroom were both very clean. The only downside was the internet connection regularly going down for a few hours at a time. Other than that, everything was perfect, a great place to stay!! :-)', 'Tours', 36, '', '', '', '', '', 9, 'Yes'),
(93, NULL, NULL, 'SangamGarg', 'SangamGarg@gmail.com', 1439817466, 'Perfect budget stay in Manali. Rooms were cozy, neat and clean. Also Adobe home is better then what we see in the images. Host was always there to guide me with everything around. We were 14 people and it was perfect home away from home. Definitely come back if I visit Manali. Also recommended for family', 'Tours', 35, '', '', '', '', '', 6, 'Yes'),
(94, NULL, NULL, 'NewtonKakadia', 'NewtonKakadia@mail.com', 1439817507, 'Hello folks!\r\nI made a 2 day 3 nights stay here in my manali trip. I would like to share my stay experience with you all.\r\nSo we arrived manali on evening and Mr Birender came to pick us up at bus station. We were 3 college friends on this trip. We shared a room. The pictures of rooms showed here in this page exactly matches. This night we had a discussion with the house owner Mr Birender regarding our trip - what we would like to do in manali, safety, precautions and everything. He arranged a taxi for us to solang valley for the very next day.\r\nNext morning, we woke up a bit late (it was too cool..hahahhh) and house owner had switched on water heater (geyser) for us an hour before we woke up. It was very nice of him to do so. As we 3 had preferred to stay in single room, we had only 1 bathroom to use. But, the house owner offered us to use extra bathroom in the next room as the room was vacant. He didn''t even take any charge for that though. Cool, they are nice people. :)\r\nThe house owner also advised us few nice budget restaurants where we could have nice food.\r\nFor the second day, he arranged the same taxi for us for kulu river rafting. We enjoyed a lot.\r\n\r\nFinally, I would say, the experience was cool, nice, awesome. They care for tourists. They helped us as a guide to manali. \r\nWhile leaving the place, we had an hour left before we could catch our reserved taxi to amritsar. So, we had a great talk with the house owner. He offered us apple fruits which he had stored for his family.\r\nLocation-This place is at walking distance to bus station. As bus station and mall road are side by, you can walk to mall road for shopping / dinner / evening walk.\r\nThanks to Mr Surender and Mr Birender for offering your stay', 'Tours', 35, '', '', '', '', '', 10, 'Yes'),
(95, NULL, NULL, 'Bong_Traveller2012', 'Bong_Traveller2012@mail.com', 1439817552, 'Adobehome accommodation looks exactly like the picture posted. The house is clean and tidy, at the same time, it is spacious as well. Surender gave detailed instructions on how to get to her accommodation with pictures included (and I must say it''s really easy to get to their place). It is a short walking distance from the Mall Manali. Upon reaching the accommodation, we saw, drinking water, cups, umbrella and even adapters on the table of our room.. It was really thoughtful of Surender. It was cold when we reached there, he immediately severed us the hot tea, it was so soothing and I am really touched by his hospitality. Surender was always quick to respond to any requests/queries.\r\n\r\nThe only negative point about the apartment is located on backside, one house after the main road and views are not good from rooms. However the terrace is open and it has 360 degree view. But it does not matter we hardly live in room and come back only in evening to sleep. \r\n\r\nI felt very comfortable and safe. Would definitely recommend anyone visiting Manali to stay at their place.', 'Tours', 35, '', '', '', '', '', 5, 'Yes'),
(96, NULL, NULL, 'Maria', 'Maria@mail.com', 1439817640, 'We were two families of 4 and 5, with young adults. The apartment met our expectations. Two bedrooms are of a very good size, and the other 3 are very small., but for one week it was not too uncomfortable. The kitchen has a dishwasher (we used it all the time), the dining room, and the living room are nice and spacious. There is washer and dryer but we never used them. The bathrooms are ok. The only problem is the noise. In the middle of the night, every night, there is loading and unloading activity at the "Freight" company across the street! If it wasn''t for that, I would say that is a perfect apartment to spend a week in NYC.', 'Tours', 35, '', '', '', '', '', 8, 'Yes'),
(97, NULL, NULL, 'happycamper', 'happycamper@mail.com', 1439817673, 'Property was in a great location. \r\nThe size was exactly what we needed for a group of 7 girls.\r\nThe place could have been a bit cleaner but it still did not ruin our trip!\r\nNo tea towels in kitchen, no lights could be turned on in kitchen area, no dishwasher, however we were told they were installing new one. Again we worked around it!\r\nWifi was off and on, but we all had use of it a one time or another.\r\nThe mouse was a little worrisome but apparently they fumigate once a month.\r\nGreat things were size and 3 full size bathrooms + 1 powder room. \r\nAwesome that bedrooms and washrooms were on top 2 floors and living space with powder room were on main floor. Lots of stairs, but hey, you''re in New York!\r\nIf we could have had early check in or late check out we would have been very happy.\r\nWe were told that they are not doing late check out anymore, however they let you leave your luggage in their office.\r\nOverall we would stay here again!', 'Tours', 35, '', '', '', '', '', 8, 'Yes'),
(98, NULL, NULL, 'Flip', 'Flip@gmail.com', 1439817720, 'My group and I stayed here in February of this year and this being our first time booking an apartment online, we were a little nervous. But when you arrived, and say this lovely home we were glad we made the choice. The location is excellent because you are so close to Central Park and some famous shopping stores. As far as eating, we had an excellent choice.\n\nThe owner was helpful and the booking process were smooth. Only one complaint that there was some trash left in the bin, but happy to recommend', 'Tours', 35, '1', '4', '1', '4', '1', 2.2, 'Yes'),
(99, NULL, NULL, 'Jon Ellen', 'jon@gmail.com', 1439817880, 'Negatives: bathroom is old, no towel racks, no electrical outlets - kitchen counters felt sticky (we stayed in January) and plates and pans were very used and mismatched, lack of counter space - hard to regulate heat, sometimes it was freezother times like a sauna - biggest issue was we left the unit cleaner than we found it and still didn''t get deposit fully refunded.', 'Tours', 35, '1', '1', '1', '5', '1', 1.8, 'Yes'),
(100, NULL, NULL, 'Maryam', 'Maryam@gmail.com', 1439817957, 'We have had the pleasure of renting apartments on two occasions from Marcia. The apartments, a studio and a one bedroom were both very comfortable and relaxing. Marcia and her staff were always available when needed. The apartments were both very clean with comfortable, new furnishings. We have visited NYC several times and enjoy living like a local in an apt with the quietness of the East side. The apartment is walkable to Central Park as well as other west side top spots. No more hotels for us!', 'Tours', 34, '', '', '', '', '', 7, 'Yes'),
(101, NULL, NULL, 'Amjad', 'amjad@gmail.com', 1439817984, 'This was our second time in an apartment managed by Mpbht & Associates and it was the same amazing experience as last year. This apartment is on the 4th floor of a beautiful townhouse building, at the back of the building, making it wonderful and quiet. My husband is a very light sleeper and very fussy with accommodation but we slept very well in this apartment. The bed is incredibly comfortable and Marcia, the principal of Mbpht & Associates uses quality linen and furnishings in the apartment. The apartment is cleaned to a very high standard before you arrive and also midway through your visit. The apartment is a one bedroom apartment, so the bedroom is separate to the lounge room and kitchen, which makes it feel nice and roomy. Both the bedroom and the main area of the apartment are air conditioned and everything worked perfectly. It was great to come back to a nice cool apartment after a really hot day and feel completely relaxed. The free wi-fi worked like a dream the whole time we were there. The kitchen is stocked with all the equipment you need to prepare a meal but we always ate out because the dining options in the area are amazing. If you do want to get some groceries in (e.g. breakfast cereals and other items) it is a short walk up Lexington to D''Agostino''s. You can walk to Central Park in 5 minutes from here. You can also walk to The Met in 15 minutes from the apartment. You are also 2 minutes walk from some great shops along Madison ave (e.g. Ralph Lauren, Juicy Couture, Nannette Lepore and many others). The apartment is in a lovely leafy street. It is quiet, upmarket and a very short walk to a number of cafes and bistros. Marcia is so wonderful to deal with. She is incredibly responsive to all your needs. These are very honest people to deal with - they are there at the apartment to greet you when they say they will be and always keep in touch with you to make sure everything is going well with the apartment.', 'Tours', 34, '', '', '', '', '', 10, 'Yes'),
(102, NULL, NULL, 'Naz', 'naz@gmail.com', 1439818015, 'Beautiful apartment in a very quiet building located next to New York''s best upscale shopping area - Madison avenue. The apartment is very close to good restaurants on Lexington avenue. Also close to Central Park, and world class museums. This is the second apartment I have stayed in in this building, and both are lovely. One has a balcony - a rarity in New York, and the other has a skylight in the bathroom.\r\nMarcia and her staff were very helpful. A great experience all around - highly recommended.', 'Tours', 34, '', '', '', '', '', 3, 'Yes'),
(103, NULL, NULL, 'Irshad A', 'nazo@gmail.com', 1439818039, 'Had a brilliant one month stay from Mid November til Mid December 2012! Apartment is huge by NY standards, and location is brilliant. 10 minute walk to 5th ave, 2 mins to CP, Subway & Shops. Well maintained, and excellent service all round. Marcia, the owner is second to none! Always accessible & happy to assist with anything day or night. As I was staying alone she also insisted on visiting to bring me vitamins & comfort foods when I came down with a cold. Truly one of a kind! The French rustic feel of the apartment is such a charm, everything worked perfectly. Would definitely stay here again!', 'Tours', 34, '', '', '', '', '', 8, 'Yes'),
(104, NULL, NULL, 'Danish', 'd@gmail.com', 1439818056, 'Thanks for writing us this wonderful review.\r\nI had post a thank you note, but didn''t see it out there.So I''m making sure this time will be published.\r\nIt was a pleasure having you as a tenant, by far you were the very first one to win the NEATEST of them all. I''m impressed with how you kept the apartment during your 30 days visit!\r\nThe unit was kept in top shape as if it was vacant, thank you for that.\r\nFeel free to use us for any reference in the US . I have only the best things to say about you. And we would love to have you back at anytime! You found a very good friend here. Thank you again.', 'Tours', 34, '', '', '', '', '', 2, 'Yes'),
(105, NULL, NULL, 'Asim', 'as@gmail.com', 1439818086, 'My family, party of 4, were in NYC to watch the USC football game. This location is superb; one of the best upscale neighborhoods in NYC. The apartment is large (for NYC), decorated nicely and very clean. Everything worked fine, Wi-Fi included. The place is nicely furnished and the sofa bed in the LR is Q-size and comfortable. \r\n\r\nMpbht & Assoc. is very professional and was reponsive and available at all times. Ms.B, the principal, was an angel and I will deal with nobody else when we return to NYC. Exceptional experience.', 'Tours', 34, '', '', '', '', '', 7, 'Yes'),
(106, NULL, NULL, 'hashim', 'hashim@gmail.com', 1439818137, 'The apartment is well located and comfortable.\r\n\r\nThey need some more kitchen utensils.\r\n\r\nThe only drawback is the cleaning lady that is a bit of a nuissance.\r\nOn check out day she came earlier and started cleaning before we left.', 'Tours', 33, '', '', '', '', '', 3, 'Yes'),
(107, NULL, NULL, 'Azhar', 'azhar@gmail.com', 1439818155, 'Hello,\r\nWe stayed in the apartment for 4 nights during our latest trip in NYC. We comfortably settled (4 adults & 1 child) and could enjoy our trip without having to worry about anything ! Felt like home. Marcia was great and helpfull from booking to check-out and treated us as friends visiting. She prepared everything with little essential goodies that made our late arrival much easier. Did I mentionned the location was perfect and so quiet ? It is. I would return & recommend', 'Tours', 33, '', '', '', '', '', 7, 'Yes'),
(108, NULL, NULL, 'John Kabla', 'Jkballa@gmail.com', 1439818180, 'Excellent location on Upper East Side, near museums and more good restaurants than you have time to try. Grocery and drug stores nearby. Also near transportation, with Madison ave and 5th ave buses nearby, plus subway just a few blocks awat. Apartment is a nice sized 1-BR. Bath is updated and apartment is at rear of building overlooking courtyard, allowing for quiet, away from the busy streets of NYC. For the location and price, a very good rental.', 'Tours', 33, '', '', '', '', '', 3, 'Yes'),
(109, NULL, NULL, 'Smith', 'sm@gmail.com', 1439818217, 'This is a one bedroom suite at the Trump Hotel at the southwest corner of Central Park. Subway is right next to hotel. Room is very nice and you recieve all hotel amenities as any other guest. Ate a good dinner with kids at the Landmark restaurant across the street in the Time Warner building (Huge Whole Foods in the lower level with a ton of prepared food). Even better dinner the next night at PJ Clarks on 63rd and Broadway in Lincoln Center (about a five minute walk). With Central Park right across the street, there is a ton of things to do in the immediate area, which overall feels cleaner than midtown.', 'Tours', 33, '', '', '', '', '', 8, 'Yes'),
(110, NULL, NULL, 'Cali Boy', 'cali@yahoo.com', 1439818257, 'Concierge, bellmen, doormen (especially 1 whose name I can''t recall) were great. The condo is comfortable and although we were wary of possible traffic noise from busy Columbus Circle, the insulation was good enough that we felt like we were in a quieter part of town. The kitchen lacks utensils to do any serious cooking, and there''s no washer/dryer like we are used to having at other similar accommodations. The gym is great, and the turndown chocolates very good. For joggers, being across the street from Central Park is a huge plus. The very large Whole Foods down the street even has a tap room now! Did not give excellent rating only because like many hotels, they didn''t call us when our unit was ready and the small lobby area got congested at times. Subway is right around the corner and having a highly acclaimed restaurant on the premises is great.', 'Tours', 32, '', '', '', '', '', 8, 'Yes'),
(111, NULL, NULL, 'Dabra hakeem', 'dab@yahoo.com', 1439818287, 'This is truly smack dab in the center of it all. We could walk to Times Square, the Theater District, and Central Park. The Subway is a short walk away. The apartment is spotless just as pictured. The bed was comfortable, and the deep set windows served as a great computer desk. Our daughter slept on the fold out couch, it was comfortable, easy to pull out and put away. The apartment is on the second floor, one flight of stairs if you don''t want to wait for the elevator. It has a few quirky things, which is to be expected for an older building, plus it made the experience authentic. \r\nThe air conditioner running on fan, created just enough white noise - you couldn''t hear the traffic - we slept well. There is a nice grocery store across the street, a drug store on the other corner, a liquor store next door, and whole foods is a short walk away. We had breakfast in the apartment every morning while we plan out our day. The price was great per NYC standards. JT is fun, and very easy', 'Tours', 32, '', '', '', '', '', 4, 'Yes'),
(112, NULL, NULL, 'salman', 'sam@yahoo.com', 1439818317, 'This apartment is in the thick of things, situated in the Broadway area with only minutes to shows and restaurants.\r\nThe accommodation is spacious and clean with a funky loft feeling.Plenty of room for 4 middle aged women to have a blast. Kitchen great if you want to cook ,however we walked down the road to 9th Ave and selected a different restaurant every night.\r\nWe walked to 3 Broadway shows and Time Square.\r\nI would definitely recommend this apartment except the tapirs are steep and it was difficult to carry our luggage up and down.\r\nThank you for making our stay the trip of a life time!!!! \r\nNEW YORK NEW YORK- I am still singing it!!! Xxxxxx', 'Tours', 32, '', '', '', '', '', 9, 'Yes'),
(113, NULL, NULL, 'Janam', 'jam@yahoo.com', 1439818346, 'This apartment is in the thick of things, situated in the Broadway area with only minutes to shows and restaurants.\r\nThe accommodation is spacious and clean with a funky loft feeling.Plenty of room for 4 middle aged women to have a blast. Kitchen great if you want to cook ,however we walked down the road to 9th Ave and selected a different restaurant every night.\r\nWe walked to 3 Broadway shows and Time Square.\r\nI would definitely recommend this apartment except the tapirs are steep and it was difficult to carry our luggage up and down.\r\nThank you for making our stay the trip of a life time!!!! \r\nNEW YORK NEW YORK- I am still singing it!!! Xxxxxx', 'Tours', 32, '', '', '', '', '', 5, 'Yes'),
(114, NULL, NULL, 'Janjua', 'jamd@yahoo.com', 1439818395, 'This property was exactly as advertised - which was great! Location is super - about a 5-7 minute walk to Times Square and lots of good restaurants all within easy walking distance. Theaters for shows were also within walking distance, as was the subway and Central Park. There were 4 adults couplesin our group so it was great to have a bedroom each. We stayed in the upstairs unit, which has 3 bedrooms and one full bathroom on the top floor, and then one bedroom and full bath on the main floor, together with a large living room, dining room and kitchen. It fit our needs perfectly for breakfasts and then a place to hang out in the evening when we got home after sightseeing. All the arrangements by Lisa were perfect - no problems with keys (it''s a keypad) and the place was nice and clean. I''d recommend it to any large groupl.', 'Tours', 32, '', '', '', '', '', 9, 'Yes'),
(115, NULL, NULL, 'Khan', 'khano@yahoo.com', 1439818421, 'This property was exactly as advertised - which was great! Location is super - about a 5-7 minute walk to Times Square and lots of good restaurants all within easy walking distance. Theaters for shows were also within walking distance, as was the subway and Central Park. There were 4 adults couplesin our group so it was great to have a bedroom each. We stayed in the upstairs unit, which has 3 bedrooms and one full bathroom on the top floor, and then one bedroom and full bath on the main floor, together with a large living room, dining room and kitchen. It fit our needs perfectly for breakfasts and then a place to hang out in the evening when we got home after sightseeing. All the arrangements by Lisa were perfect - no problems with keys (it''s a keypad) and the place was nice and clean. I''d recommend it to any large groupl.', 'Tours', 32, '', '', '', '', '', 3, 'Yes'),
(116, NULL, NULL, 'Loby', 'lob@gmai.com', 1439818456, '7 of us aged from 19 to 52 stayed here for 7 days in June. The upper apartment was ideal for us, spacious, spotless and ideally located. It''s within walking distance to Central Park, Times Sq, Top of the Rock, and the Hudson. The Subway station is 1 block away and you can get to anywhere from it - we went to WTC, Empire State, Coney Island and the Baseball to name just a few - get the $30 weekly pass, it''s a steal.We found loads of fantastic local restaurants all within walking distance - El Centro and La Masseria Dei Vini were our favourites!\r\nWe highly recommend the apartment, it''s as good as the pictures on the website, and Lisa dealt with all our queries very promptly and efficiently - we will definitely book it again when we return in a few years time!', 'Tours', 30, '', '', '', '', '', 9, 'Yes'),
(117, NULL, NULL, 'Shair', 'sahir@gmai.com', 1439818479, '7 of us aged from 19 to 52 stayed here for 7 days in June. The upper apartment was ideal for us, spacious, spotless and ideally located. It''s within walking distance to Central Park, Times Sq, Top of the Rock, and the Hudson. The Subway station is 1 block away and you can get to anywhere from it - we went to WTC, Empire State, Coney Island and the Baseball to name just a few - get the $30 weekly pass, it''s a steal.We found loads of fantastic local restaurants all within walking distance - El Centro and La Masseria Dei Vini were our favourites!\r\nWe highly recommend the apartment, it''s as good as the pictures on the website, and Lisa dealt with all our queries very promptly and efficiently - we will definitely book it again when we return in a few years time!', 'Tours', 30, '', '', '', '', '', 5, 'Yes'),
(118, NULL, NULL, 'Mehbob', 'maah@gmai.com', 1439818507, 'Eight ladies stayed in this apartment over 11 days. The apartment was very generous in size giving us room to move without tripping over each other. It was nicely furnished and decorated, the beds were really comfy and so were the couches. Another plus was not having to use traditional keys to enter the premises. The kitchen had all manner of utensils and appliances should you wish to cook (we only made breakfast). There were a couple of minor maintenance issues with the tap ware in the bathrooms however, the owner is having these all replaced soon. The owners do request guests to remove their shoes to keep the carpet on the stairs as clean as possible (understandable) however, this then makes the stairs very slippery when descending - several slipped and one broke a toe on the last day of our stay. The location of the apartment was outstanding, could not have asked for better. We could walk to so many places/attractions with ease. We sampled three of the restaurants (one twice) in our street plus a bar and enjoyed them all. Easy access to the subway and also convenience/grocery stores.\r\nAll in all this apartment made our stay that much more enjoyable.', 'Tours', 30, '', '', '', '', '', 8, 'Yes');
INSERT INTO `pt_reviews` (`review_id`, `review_booking_id`, `review_user`, `review_name`, `review_email`, `review_date`, `review_comment`, `review_module`, `review_itemid`, `review_clean`, `review_comfort`, `review_location`, `review_facilities`, `review_staff`, `review_overall`, `review_status`) VALUES
(119, NULL, NULL, 'masoom', 'masoom@gmail.com', 1439818564, 'We stayed in this townhouse in March of 2015. It was a mother/daughter springbreak trip for our daughters’ senior year of high school. We had a total of 8 people and the house was great! It looks just like it does in the pictures. It was so nice after a busy day of sightseeing to be able to come back to the townhouse and relax all together. The living room/dining room area was very comfortable for all of us to be together. The location was perfect for us! We were able walk to Times Square, Rockefeller Center, the Circle Line Pier, Broadway shows and train lines. It was the first time to New York for most of our group and we found the city easy to navigate from where we were. There were numerous restaurants close by and a number of grocery and pharmacies within walking distance. We stayed in the upper unit and the only warning I would offer to people is that the stairs are steep and you will be climbing 2 flights of stairs often. There is a lower unit available that might be a good choice if the stairs are a challenge for you. \r\nThe owner was very responsive to our questions. We would definitely recommend this rental to our friends!', 'Tours', 29, '', '', '', '', '', 9, 'Yes'),
(120, NULL, NULL, 'Masnha', 'masooms@gmail.com', 1439818587, 'We were a group of eight adults, and it was the perfect place for us .Terrific location! So close to the subway that you could get anywhere in Manhattan in minutes. Tempting restaurants right on the same block: Ippudo and The Brew House were great finds! \r\n\r\nLisa was easy to work with, and her charming home was just as described. Four spacious bedrooms with comfy beds; a nice living and dining room where all eight of us could hang out together. So much better than staying in four hotel rooms, as we could lounge about together in the mornings.\r\n\r\nWe''d love to come stay again!', 'Tours', 29, '', '', '', '', '', 3, 'Yes'),
(121, NULL, NULL, 'Mahi', 'mahi@gmail.com', 1439818622, 'My group of 6 stayed at this beautiful flat for a family vacation and it was amazing! Our stay was picture perfect, from the great location and super easy and straightforward access to the flat to the comfortable beds with nice linens, fully equipped kitchen, and beautifully appointed and cozy living room that was so nice for gathering with the family. \r\n\r\nThe neighborhood is great - very close to Times Square and the theaters. We walked everywhere - to Central Park, Midtown, Rockefeller Center, St. Patrick''s Cathedral. Super close to the subway station for longer trips. The street itself has several nice cafes and restaurants, and there was a great little market only 2 blocks away as well. \r\n\r\nThis place is a gem and we couldn''t have been more pleased. I hope it''s available the next time we come to New York.', 'Tours', 29, '', '', '', '', '', 7, 'Yes'),
(122, NULL, NULL, 'Raza', 'mah3i@gmail.com', 1439818639, 'Property is very large for NYC, especially the bedrooms which all had a reading chair and storage which provides quiet space for everyone when you are travelling with a big group for a week. Location is awesome, both for walking in neighbourhood and access to the subway. Rental process was straight forward and communication with the owner was fluid. A good option for anyone needing a big property.', 'Tours', 29, '', '', '', '', '', 3, 'Yes'),
(123, NULL, NULL, 'Amjad', 'amjad@gmail.com', 1439818699, 'A group of 8 of us rented the apartment for 6 days and it was absolutely perfect in every way, spotlessly clean, spacious and a perfect location to see the sights of NYC. We only had one problem which was Wifi access and emailed Lisa and she responded within 10 minutes and sorted it straight away for us. All 8 of the party agreed the apartment was a fantastic place to stay and great value for money, and every room in the apartment was bigger than you would experience in any hotel. We would all recommend this place to stay and would definitely book again if and when we decide to return to NYC, hopefully next time we won''t have any snow!', 'Tours', 28, '', '', '', '', '', 9, 'Yes'),
(124, NULL, NULL, 'Nasir', 'nasjad@gmail.com', 1439818717, 'We booked this apartment for a family holiday to New York City and couldn''t have chosen a better place to call home for 2 weeks! This gorgeous brownstone is beautifully presented and we were so impressed with how spacious and comfortable the apartment was. Everyone was expecting something much smaller for NYC! The location is fantastic for those wanting to enjoy Broadway, Central Park, Times Square and 5th Avenue shopping. There are endless dining options within walking distance and 9th Avenue has a great variety of fantastic restaurants. Lisa was a pleasure to deal with and nothing was ever too much trouble. She even provided a christmas tree stand and ornaments so we could have a Christmas Tree. Highly recommend this apartment and guarantee you won''t be disappointed! We are from Australia and it might be a long time before we return to NYC, but if we do, we would definitely stay here again!!', 'Tours', 28, '', '', '', '', '', 4, 'Yes'),
(125, NULL, NULL, 'Saad', 'saad@gmail.com', 1439818774, 'This apartment has 4 doubled bedrooms Large! You will not want for anything here, just fantastic would recommend it to family, couples for girlfriends! Close to Times Square, Broadway plus 3 subways not far at all! You can walk to 5th Avenue! Apartment is in Hells Kitchen area so it is noisy I have to say so good ear plugs are needed! Well you are in the city that never sleeps! You need to do all the New York stuff! I loved it and can''t wait to get back there! A couple of MUST see 911 museum, walk in Brooklyn Bridge, Empire State, a ride in Central Park and a helicopter ride!', 'Tours', 26, '', '', '', '', '', 5, 'Yes'),
(126, NULL, NULL, 'Rafeek', 'rf@gmail.com', 1439819599, 'We stayed for a week,the family age ranged from 2 to 74.it was lovely to be all together with such good facilities , 4 spacious bedrooms, huge living area, kitchen well equipped though with such good local shops we did not cook much, 2 bathrooms, toilets and a laundry room.there were a lot of stairs but we coped with them .\r\n\r\nIt is very central within easy walking distance of many sights, the runners in the family went to Central Park on several early morning runs, the children enjoyed the space, toys and large television.grandma did not find time to read any of the many books left in the rooms.\r\n\r\nWe would recommend it to any group seeking a comfortable well situated apartment.', 'Tours', 26, '', '', '', '', '', 3, 'Yes'),
(127, NULL, NULL, 'Majid', 'majid@gmail.com', 1439819683, 'My family and I recently stayed in the Upper Unit and we can''t speak more highly of the standard of accommodation and the level of service. Lisa is a travel industry professional (a rarity when trying to rent apartments in cities like New York.) She was responsive and helpful from the initial request and continued to stay in touch with us until the time we returned back home. She also kindly accommodated some special requests regarding early arrival and late departure. \r\n\r\nWe were a party of 5 including 2 small children. The space was more than comfortable, with enough space to ensure that we weren''t all on top of one another. The kitchen was fully stocked with all the equipment one would need to make meals at home and the bathrooms (much like the rest of the apartment) were pristine. There is some street noise, which is expected in midtown Manhattan...but it wasn''t at all bothersome. Beds are comfy, there are plenty of plush towels, and bed linens are crisp and of a high standard. \r\n\r\nThe only thing that was slightly awkward with 2 strollers were the stairs --- however, we saw this as a positive! While none of us appreciated how many stairs lead up to the front door and then up to the main level of the upper unit, the adults were grateful for the extra work out. Thank you for a lovely stay. We will be back.', 'Tours', 26, '', '', '', '', '', 7, 'Yes'),
(128, NULL, NULL, 'Sam', 'sam@gmail.com', 1439819711, 'We had an excellent stay in this well appointed and fabulously located. It never felt crowded, with 5 of us. Close to all amenities, aircon works very well indeed. Kitchen is great, beds comfortable. Free wifi very good also. So good we barely had the TV on at all for 10 days!', 'Tours', 26, '', '', '', '', '', 3, 'Yes'),
(129, NULL, NULL, 'kamwali', 'kamwali@gmail.com', 1439819803, 'We had an excellent stay in this well appointed and fabulously located. It never felt crowded, with 5 of us. Close to all amenities, aircon works very well indeed. Kitchen is great, beds comfortable. Free wifi very good also. So good we barely had the TV on at all for 10 days!', 'Tours', 24, '', '', '', '', '', 9, 'Yes'),
(130, NULL, NULL, 'Kachalo', 'kamwdali@gmail.com', 1439819821, 'We absolutely loved this place! We were four couples (the husbands were all brothers) traveling to the city to celebrate our anniversaries. The location of this property was perfect and within walking distance to so many of the sights that we wanted to see. It was also spacious enough that we didn''t feel like we were on top of each other all the time. The bedrooms were incredibly large and there was plenty of seating for all 8 of us. At the end of the trip, everyone said they would definitely stay here again if we do another trip to NY.\r\n\r\nLisa was very responsive when we contacted her, and always responded within 24 hours. Prior to booking this location I had inquired at several other properties that met our requirements (4 bedrooms, minimum of 2 baths, location, etc). Lisa was the only one who responded to my inquiries. Others used automated email responses, but whenever I had a follow-up question I could never get a response - even if I called. Just adding this as a caution to others. If I hadn''t been able to reserve this property with Lisa, I was considering a trip to NY just to confirm the validity of a property before booking...', 'Tours', 24, '', '', '', '', '', 5, 'Yes'),
(131, NULL, NULL, 'Raheem', 'rah@gmail.com', 1439819837, 'Location was ideal - broad range of restaurants to suit every pocket. Subway system, Times Square, Broadway, Central Park etc within walking distance.Yes it is on a ''quieter'' street considering its central location but remember this is a relative term. \r\nWe found the cleaning crew and Lisa to be very attentive and I would say the photos and previous reviews are a true reflection of the apartment', 'Tours', 24, '', '', '', '', '', 7, 'Yes'),
(132, NULL, NULL, 'faith', 'fath@gmail.com', 1439819858, 'Family trip, three generations, lots of room, nicely appointed, and the location cannot be beat (at this price). Not perfect, Lisa could pay a little more attention to the details. No tissues, furniture ready to fall apart, floor was dirty despite our dutifully removing shoes at the bottom of the stairs. But overall a great place to stay.', 'Tours', 24, '', '', '', '', '', 3, 'Yes'),
(133, NULL, NULL, 'John', 'fadth@gmail.com', 1439819889, '''m late in posting this but our stay was great so it''s worthy of this delayed review.\r\n\r\nThank you Lisa for your prompt, friendly & professional interaction. It made the booking easy & positive. It was a relief to confirm the legal situation of the property too.\r\n\r\nThis house provided us with a comfortable, well presented, spacious & convenient home away from home. \r\n\r\nWe walked everywhere from this location, even with three 12yo boys who dislike walking! Times Sq,Radio City,Rockerfeller Ctr, & Broadway were an easy walk. The subway is convenient, & taxis were a quick ride too. Local restaurants & supermarkets are great. Whole Foods & Amish Market are nearby, and just down the street there''s great restaurants & a wine bar. A pharmacy/convenience store for late night needs is just a block down 9th. \r\n\r\nThe home is clean & well laid out, and the bathrooms easily serviced our group of 7. Beds & bedding were ridiculously fresh and comfortable and there was ample wardrobe/luggage space. The laundry was fully equipped, as was the kitchen, and we shared family dinners comfortably in the dining area.\r\n\r\nAll appliances & electronics worked well, & the guest information folder provided good information on the property and local amenities. \r\n\r\nThe only concern for some of us was that we felt the cold a bit in the living room. A few extra throws would have been handy. The heating is automatically set, & cannot be adjusted but it was mostly sufficient and not an overriding concern. It was certainly warm enough for sleeping in the bedrooms. \r\n\r\nThe neighbourhood was good, felt safe enough walking at night. A bit noisy in a typical NYC way but nothing major. You could hear it from the rear bedrooms but it wasn''t too distracting & we come from a quiet spot in the Blue Mountains. \r\n\r\nI definitely recommend this property & vendor to anyone seeking accommodation in Manhattan. When we return, we hope to book it again. \r\n\r\nThanks Lisa for listing a rare legal gem in the heart of a fabulous city!', 'Tours', 24, '', '', '', '', '', 5, 'Yes'),
(134, NULL, NULL, 'Sehra', 'se@gmal.com', 1441988537, 'This is one of the best hotel which I visited in my life.', 'Hotels', 34, '3', '4', '8', '5', '8', 5.6, 'Yes'),
(135, NULL, NULL, 'Addmi', 'h@g.com', 1441988620, 'I have seen some bad luck but overall the hotel is on good location.', 'Hotels', 34, '8', '6', '6', '2', '5', 5.4, 'Yes'),
